{
  "texts": [
    "Table 5 displays indicators for the three main LLMs.",
    "In a few models, the error in prediction is well predicted by socio-demographic variables.",
    "This is for instance the case of religious attendance by Mixtral (R 2 ≃.74), or trust and politics by GPT (R 2 ≃.57).",
    "On the 8 other models we evaluated, the R 2 is quite low, with a median of.36.",
    "We conclude from these indicators that socio-demographics have a weak to moderate correlation with the LLMs' prediction error, and that social bias fails to predict the major part of this error."
  ]
}